    <div id="whatis">
    <p>Compulsive Dabbing Disorder (or CDD) is a medical condition in which the patient develops a psychological need to dab at inopportune moments. In nearly 100% of cases, it results in social isolation for the patient and intense suffering for those around him/her. If you or a loved one begins to show signs of CDD, get help immediately. </p><br>
